  'folder': "computer-systems",
  'content': "# Quick Reference\n\n> Problem \u2192 solution lookup table for concurrency.\n\n\n| Problem | Hardware Cause | Solution |\n|---------|---------------|----------|\n| **Data race** | Two cores' load-modify-store sequences interleave | Mutex, atomics, or redesign to avoid sharing |\n| **Deadlock** | Circular wait: each core blocked in FUTEX_WAIT on the other's lock | Consistent lock ordering, `std::scoped_lock` |\n| **Livelock** | Cores actively executing but constantly yielding | Random backoff, tiebreaker priority |\n| **Starvation** | Scheduler/hardware never gives one core the resource | Fair mutex, priority inheritance |\n| **False sharing** | Two cores write different bytes on same 64-byte cache line \u2192 MESI ping-pong | `alignas(64)` per-thread data |\n| **High lock contention** | Cores spending cycles in FUTEX_WAIT, not doing work | Reader-writer lock, lock-free structure, sharding |\n| **Low lock contention (short CS)** | Futex overhead > critical section time | Spinlock for < 1 \u00b5s critical sections |\n| **Spurious wakeup** | Kernel wakes FUTEX_WAIT without notify | Always use `cv.wait(lock, predicate)` |\n| **Relaxed ordering bug** | Store buffer reordering \u2192 consumer sees stale data | `acquire` on read, `release` on write |\n\n---"
